{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2393"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of other porcelain and ceramic products"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2393"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :porcelain-ceramic-products/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :materials-safety :resource-efficiency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :porcelain-ceramic-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "PorcelainAdvisor ⊣ Porcelain/Ceramic Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for porcelain/ceramic-products (tableware, decorative ceramics,
 technical/industrial ceramics) plants (raw-material (kaolin/feldspar/
 quartz) forming (jiggering/jolleying/RAM-pressing/slip-casting) ->
 glazing -> kiln-firing -> inspection production line) -- not direct
 forming-line/kiln-line-equipment control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Eleven concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct forming/kiln-
 line-equipment control), permanent forming/kiln-line-actuate block,
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-weight recompute against
 the batch's own logged weight, double-schedule guard, product-type
 validation, glaze-defect-rate plausibility validation, and
 chip-resistance plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging
 (kiln-safety/glaze-material-safety -- lead-free glaze compliance)
 ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch`
 is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
